@Charles Nelson Reilly 

I was in Pompeii twice, in 1995 and 2024. It is a fascinating place, but so run down it hurts to watch in places. The current administration of the excavations is trying its best to prevent further damage, but decades of neglect took their toll. Also, the site is so large you either have to spend two or three days there, at least - to see all of it - or rush from site to site in one day, only to be left with a feeling of having missed out on a fuller experience. 

Herculaneum is more interesting, in a way - it is much smaller, so you can see everything in detail in one day, and it is also better preserved, as it was covered by a much thicker layer of volcanic material - some buildings are complete, roofs and all, with wooden furnishings and furniture. It is incredible.

